An unincorporated nonprofit association may file a certificate of association with the Secretary of State containing:
The name of the association meeting the requirements of KRS 14A.6-010;
The mailing address of the association's initial principal office;
The name and address of the association's registered agent and registered office, both meeting the requirements of KRS 14A.4-010; and
A statement of the association's purpose.
